ications%20is%20targeted%20at%20different%20user%20needs.%20Here's%20how%20they%20break%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFacebook%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFacebook%20is%20by%20far%20the%20oldest%20platform%20under%20the%20Meta%20umbrella%20and%2C%20indeed%2C%20was%20what%20Meta%20was%20originally%20named%20after.%20Facebook%20was%20founded%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwho-owns-facebook%5C%22%3EMark%20Zuckerberg%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0nearly%20two%20decades%20ago%20in%202004.%20It's%20grown%20to%20be%20among%20the%20largest%20social%20networks%20to%20exist%2C%20with%20over%20two%20billion%20active%20monthly%20users.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20most%20social%20media%20users%20from%20the%20early%202010s%20and%20prior%20started%20on%20this%20platform%2C%20over%20the%20past%20few%20years%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ffacebook-gen-z-teens-boomer-social-network-leaks-2021-10%5C%22%3EFacebook's%20user%20demographics%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20been%20publicly%20perceived%20as%20having%20shifted%2C%20largely%20skewing%20to%20older%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch3%3EFacebook%20Messenger%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EOriginally%20a%20part%20of%20the%20Facebook%20app%20itself%20on%20all%20platforms%2C%20Messenger%20is%20now%20a%20standalone%20app.%20The%20private%20messaging%20app%20for%20mobile%20devices%20exists%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-secret-second-website-messenger-com-app-desktop-2016-1%23in-plain-white-it-doesnt-even-look-like-facebook-which-could-be-a-godsend-in-offices-where-the-social-network-is-banned-8%5C%22%3Ea%20secret%20option%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20those%20using%20desktop%20computers%20and%20laptops%20in%20places%20where%20the%20Facebook%20domain%20may%20be%20blocked.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Ffacebook-messenger-not-working%5C%22%3EFacebook%20Messenger%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20you%20can%20privately%20message%20with%20other%20users%20and%20even%20take%20part%20in%20group%20messages.%20Some%20Facebook%20users%20opt%20to%20use%20Messenger%20as%20a%20way%20to%20communicate%20with%20their%20relatives%20who%20are%20still%20active%20on%20the%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EInstagram%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-instagram-how-to-use-guide%5C%22%3EInstagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20photo-%20and%20video-based%20social%20network%20that%20was%20created%20by%20Kevin%20Systrom%20and%20Mike%20Krieger%20in%202010.%20It%20quickly%20grew%20to%20over%20a%20million%20users%20just%20two%20months%20after%20the%20launch%20of%20its%20iOS%20app.%20Two%20years%20later%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-buys-instagram-2012-4%5C%22%3EFacebook%20bought%20Instagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20%241%20billion%20in%20cash%20and%20stock.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20time%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffacebook-instagram-college-no-degree-job-jay-hammonds%5C%22%3Eacquisition%2C%20Instagram%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20fewer%20than%2017%20employees%20but%20quickly%20grew%20to%201%2C500.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20first%20years%20of%20its%20existence%2C%20the%20platform%20catered%20mostly%20towards%20picture-based%20content%2C%20allowing%20for%20shorter%20text%20descriptions%20without%20the%20features%20found%20on%20Facebook%2C%20such%20as%20internal%20links.%20However%2C%20the%20platform%20has%20pivoted%20throughout%20its%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202016%2C%20Instagram%20adopted%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsnapchat-employee-reacted-to-similiarities-of-instagram-stories-2016-8%5C%22%3EInstagram%20Stories%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0for%20short-form%20media%20content%20that%20expires%20after%2024%20hours.%20The%20move%20was%20seen%20as%20following%20on%20the%20success%20of%20disappearing%20content%20on%20Snapchat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20TikTok%20rose%20to%20prominence%2C%20Instagram%20pivoted%20once%