rest%20of%20their%20lives.%20Several%20of%20these%20troops%20were%20awarded%20Purple%20Hearts%20in%20recognition%20of%20their%20injuries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUS%20Army%20Maj.%20Robert%20Hales%20was%20the%20highest-ranking%20medical%20doctor%20on%20the%20base%20during%20the%20attack.%20In%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DlGP7hZQuTL0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20interview%20with%2060%20Minutes%3C%2Fa%3E%20over%20a%20year%20later%2C%20he%20said%20there%20is%20limited%20understanding%20of%20brain%20traumas%20such%20an%20attack%20can%20cause.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20hasn't%20been%20a%20lot%20of%20studies%20with%20this%20level%20of%20percussion%20wave%2C%20with%20the%20overpressure%20and%20the%20negative%20pressure%20that%20immediately%20follows%20being%20exposed%20to%20this%2C%20over%20and%20over%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BJust%20because%20this%20missile%20attack%20was%20so%20unique%2C%20as%20it%20never%20has%20happened%20in%20history%20that%20a%20ground%20force%20was%20exposed%20to%2011%20theatre%20ballistic%20missiles.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC10344429%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20in%20August%20by%20the%20Journal%20of%20the%20American%20College%20of%20Surgeons%2C%20TBIs%20will%20only%20become%20%26quot%3Bmore%20prevalent%26quot%3B%20among%20US%20troops%20in%20conflicts%20against%20a%20near-peer%20adversary%2C%20a%20term%20that%20refers%20to%20forces%20with%20capabilities%20similar%20to%20those%20of%20the%20US%20military.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22946%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iran%20ballistic%20missile%20Iraq%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ececc415cc5d00198c73fc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22711%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDebris%20from%20Iranian%20missiles%20seen%20in%20a%20rural%20area%20near%20Erbil%20on%20January%208%2C%202020.%3Cp%3EAl-Baghdadi%20township%2FHandout%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20post-2001%20wars%2C%20the%20US%20found%20itself%20fighting%20insurgents%20and%20terrorist%20groups%20who%20used%20unconventional%20tactics%20to%20counter%20the%20US's%20military%20and%20technological%20superiority.%20US%20dominance%20of%20the%20air%2C%20ground%2C%20and%20sea%20%26quot%3Bassured%20relative%20freedom%20of%20movement%20for%20medical%20evacuation%26quot%3B%20of%20wounded%20US%20troops%2C%20the%20report%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%2060%2C000%20casualties%2C%20including%207%2C076%20deaths%2C%20that%20the%20US%20suffered%20in%20those%20wars%20were%20caused%20by%20small-arms%20fire%20and%20less%20sophisticated%20weapons%20like%20improvised%20explosive%20devices%2C%20mortars%2C%20and%20small%20rockets.%20As%20the%20fighting%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20shown%2C%20a%20war%20against%20a%20near-peer%20adversary%20would%20almost%20certainly%20involve%20heavier%20and%20longer-range%20weaponry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%2070%25%20of%20Ukraine's%20combat%20casualties%20are%20from%20Russian%20artillery%20and%20rocket%20barrages%2C%20which%20cause%20%26quot%3Bmultiple%20high-velocity%20penetrating%20injuries%2C%20barotrauma%2C%20and%20blunt%20injuries%20from%20being%20thrown%20during%20the%20explosion%26quot%3B%20and%2C%20of%20course%2C%20TBIs%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report%2C%20which%20notes%20that%20attacks%20using%20IEDs%20%26quot%3Baffected%20fewer%20patients%2C%20in%20general%2C%20and%20caused%20less%20severe%20injury.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20highlights%20the%20Al%20Asad%20attack%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Brare%20modern%20instance%26quot%3B%20of%20US%20troops%20facing%20near-peer%20adversary-level%20weapons%20and%20suffering%20significant%20numbers%20of%20debilitating%20TBIs%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Army%20casualty%20Blackhawk%20helicopter%20medevac%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64ece9b915cc5d00198c703d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221335%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20soldiers%20carry%20a%20simulated%20casualty%20to%20a%20helicopter%20during%20a%20medevac%20exercise%20in%20Vermont%20in%20August%202017.%3Cp%3EUS%20Air%20National%20Guard%2FTech.%20Sgt.%20Sarah%20Mattison%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMoreover%2C%20it%20would%20be%20much%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-china-militaries-train-new-ways-to-medevac-wounded-troops-2023-8%5C%22%3Eharder%20to%20evacuate%20wounded%20personnel%20from%20the%20battlefield%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20given%20the%20likelihood%20that%20a%20near-peer%20adversary%20will%20field%20long-range%20sensors%20and%20weapons%20capable%20of%20reaching%20far%20behind%20the%20frontline.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20especially%20true%20of%20air%20evacuation.%20The%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20shown%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-general-surprised-russian-failure-against-ukraine-soviet-era-defenses-2023-8%5C%22%3Ehow%20tough%20air%20operations%20would%20be%20against%20a%20near-peer%20adversary%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20recent%20campaigns%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20provide%20examples%20of%20how%20even%20less%20capable%20enemies%20can%20use%20cheap%20drones%20to%20contest%20the%20airspace%20over%20the%20battlefield.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESmall%20and%20medium-size%20drones%20are%20proliferating%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20%26quot%3Bpresent%20a%20new%20and%20complex%20threat%20to%20our%20forces%20and%20those%20of%20our%20partners%20and%20allies%2C%26quot%3B%20US%20Marine%20Corps%20Gen.%20Kenneth%20McKenzie%20told%20the%20Senate%20Armed%20Services%20Committee%20in%20April%202021.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20first%20time%20since%20the%20Korean%20War%2C%20we%20are%20operating%20without%20complete%20air%20superiority%2C%26quot%3B%20added%20McKenzie%2C%20who%20was%20head%20of%20US%20Central%20Command%20at%20the%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20likelihood%20of%20a%20war%20or%20even%20a%20limited%20conflict%20with%20a%20near-peer%20adversary%20rises%20and%20the%20US%20military's%20longstanding%20advantages%20erode%2C%20it%20is%20increasingly%20necessary%20to%20develop%20techniques%20to%20prevent%20and%20treat%20TBIs.%20The%20Al%20Asad%20attack%20was%20a%20relatively%20small-scale%20demonstration%20of%20the%20lethal%20dangers%20that%20US%20troops%20will%20face%20on%20the%20battlefields%20of%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPaul%20Iddon%20is%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20and%20columnist%20who%20writes%20about%20Middle%20East%20developments%2C%20military%20affairs%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20history.%20His%20articles%20have%20appeared%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20publications%20focused%20on%20the%20region.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-iraq-ballistic-missile-attack-us-troops-traumatic-brain-injury-2023-8%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693260421000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e2b2c3ae0e1444790634556%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-iraq-ballistic-missile-attack-us-troops-traumatic-brain-injury-2023-8%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20strike%20considered%20%26quot%3Bthe%20largest%20ballistic%20attack%20against%20Americans%20in%20history%26quot%3B%20was%20likely%20only%20a%20preview%20of%20what%20US%20troops%20would%20face%20in%20future%20wars.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Paul%20Iddon)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A24%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Firan-iraq-ballistic-missile-attack-us-troops-traumatic-brain-injury-2023-8%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUr