opener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F1ac68c09-3b06-4dad-bdcc-febaa9a3961d%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Financial%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BGiven%20that%20a%20systemic%20crisis%20in%20China%20would%20reverberate%20around%20the%20world%2C%20this%20has%20raised%20alarm%20and%20triggered%20calls%20for%20Beijing%20to%20intervene%20more%20forcefully%20to%20revive%20the%20Chinese%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Gave%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20curious%20thing%2C%20though%2C%20is%20that%20such%20doom%20and%20gloom%20is%20not%20reflected%20in%20what%20the%20market%20is%20signaling.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20a%20first-quarter%20bounce%2C%20China's%20economic%20rebound%20from%20zero-COVID%20policies%20has%20been%20disappointing%2C%20with%20factories%20and%20consumers%20slowing%20down.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20property%20market%20continues%20to%20crumble%20under%20the%20weight%20of%20debt%20and%20defaults%2C%20youth%20unemployment%20is%20at%20a%20record%20high%2C%20and%20consumer%20prices%20have%20hit%20deflation%20territory.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20foreign%20investors%20have%20withdrawn%20in%20droves%2C%20with%20Beijing's%20attempts%20to%20support%20its%20markets%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fchina-stock-market-rescue-economy-debt-deflation-unemployment-growth-crisis-2023-8%3F_gl%3D1*1godikf*_ga*MTMxNDIwNDI1Ni4xNjc1Njg3OTU4*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY5MzI0NzU3Mi4xMi4xLjE2OTMyNTAxNDUuNjAuMC4w%5C%22%3Efailing%20to%20produce%20a%20sustained%C2%A0rally%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Gave%20cited%20other%20indicators%20that%20present%20a%20different%20take%20on%20the%20Chinese%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFocusing%20on%20the%20banking%20sector%2C%20he%20noted%20that%20the%20share%20price%20performance%20of%20lenders%20tends%20to%20drop%20months%20ahead%20of%20any%20systemic%20crisis%2C%20as%20had%20happened%20before%202008%20global%20financial%