fits%20might%20ameliorate%20that.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMiddle-class%20wages%20and%20household%20incomes%20have%20stagnated%20in%20recent%20decades%2C%26quot%3B%20Janet%20Yellen%2C%20the%20Treasury%20secretary%2C%20said%20in%20a%20press%20call.%20%26quot%3BBoth%20renting%20and%20owning%20a%20home%20have%20become%20more%20expensive%20and%20so%20have%20education%20and%20healthcare.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMiddle-class%20workers%2C%20whom%20the%20Treasury%20defines%20as%20falling%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20the%20national%20income%20distribution%20and%20by%20markers%20such%20as%20owning%20a%20home%20or%20being%20able%20to%20afford%20a%20college%20education%2C%20have%20seen%20real%20wages%20barely%20grow%2C%20income%20volatility%20increase%2C%20house%20prices%20skyrocket%2C%20and%20debt-to-income%20ratios%20more%20than%20double.%20Many%20are%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaying-bills-credit-card-debt-student-loans-2023-8%5C%22%3Econtending%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20student-loan%20and%20mortgage%20debt%2C%20leaving%20them%20unable%20to%20save%20for%20retirement.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20decline%20in%20intergenerational%20mobility%20may%20be%20the%20single%20trend%20that%20best%20encapsulates%20the%20pervasive%20sense%20of%20the%20deterioration%20in%20the%20middle%20class%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20Treasury%20report%20found.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20where%20unions%20can%20come%20in%2C%20Yellen%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20findings%20challenge%20arguments%20that%20unions%20hold%20back%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20Yellen%20said.%20%26quot%3BUnions%20could%20contribute%20to%20reversing%20the%20stark%20increase%20in%20inequality%20we've%20seen%20in%20recent%20decades%2C%20promoting%20economy-wide%20growth.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20the%20past%2050%20years%2C%20middle-class%20wages%20have%20stagnated%2C%20with%20middle-class%20workers%20still%20earning%20less%20than%20the%20highest%20earners'%20median%20income%20in%201970.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famericas-middle-class-shrinks-as-richest-households-make-more-2022-4%5C%22%3EPew%20Research%20Center%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20share%20of%20adults%20living%20in%20middle-class%20households%20fell%20from%2061%25%20in%201971%20to%2050%25%20in%202021.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Treasury%20report%20found%20that%20union%20workers%20make%2010%25%20to%2015%25%20more%20than%20nonunionized%20colleagues.%20That's%20one%20economic%20factor%20that%20could%20give%20union%20workers%20%E2%80%94%20who%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20be%20considered%20middle%20class%20%E2%80%94%20a%20boost.%20But%20beyond%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbeing-in-union-make-1-million-dollars-more-over-lifetime-2022-10%5C%22%3Ehigher%20pay%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20union%20workers%20are%20five%20times%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20what's%20called%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dol.gov%2Fgeneral%2Ftopic%2Fretirement%2Ftypesofplans%23%3A~%3Atext%3DA%2520defined%2520benefit%2520plan%2520promises%2C%2524100%2520per%2520month%2520at%2520retirement.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edefined-benefit%20retirement%20plans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20meaning%20that%20their%20retirement%20funds%20will%20guarantee%20a%20specific%20monthly%20payout%20once%20they're%20no%20longer%20working.%20Union%20workers%20are%20more%20likely%20to%20know%20their%20schedules%20ahead%20of%20time%2C%20cutting%20down%20on%20scheduling%20instability%20and%20effectively%20putting%20more%20money%20in%20their%20pockets%20since%20they're%20able%20to%20plan%20ahead%20for%20things%20like%20childcare.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnion%20workers%20are%20also%20more%20likely%20to%20have%20paid%20sick%20leave%2C%20medical%20benefits%2C%20subsidized%20commuting%2C%20and%20even%20more%20likely%20to%20receive%20unemployment%20insurance%20should%20they%20get%20laid%20off%20%E2%80%94%20which%20the%20report%20finds%20i