rendra_Modi_and_Vladimir_Putin_2022-09-16.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20personally%20informed%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20over%20phone%20on%20Monday%2C%20August%2028%2C%20that%20he%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20attend%20the%20G-20%20summit%20next%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%20had%20already%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fvladimir-putin-will-not-attend-g20-summit-india%5C%22%3Eannounced%3C%2Fa%3E%20last%20Friday%20that%20Putin%20would%20not%20be%20travelling%20to%20India%20as%20he%20was%20concentrating%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Cspecial%20military%20operation%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20is%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmea.gov.in%2Fpress-releases.htm%3Fdtl%2F37056%2FPrime%2BMinister%2Bspeaks%2Bwith%2BPresident%2Bof%2Bthe%2BRussian%2BFederation%5C%22%3Ereadout%3C%2Fa%3E%20issued%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20on%20Monday%2C%20August%2028%2C%20announced%20that%20President%20Putin%20%E2%80%9Cconveyed%20his%20inability%E2%80%9D%20to%20attend%20the%20summit%20slated%20to%20be%20held%20on%20September%209-10.%20He%20also%20said%20that%20Russia%20would%20be%20represented%20by%20its%20foreign%20minister%20Sergey%20Lavrov.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhile%20expressing%20an%20understanding%20for%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20decision%2C%20PM%20thanked%20President%20Putin%20for%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20consistent%20support%20to%20all%20initiatives%20under%20India%E2%80%99s%20G20%20Presidency%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20the%20Indian%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fkremlin.ru%2Fevents%2Fpresident%2Fnews%2F72135%5C%22%3Epress%20release%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20conversation%20was%20silent%20on%20the%20absence%20of%20Putin%20from%20the%20G-20%20summit.%20%E2%80%9CAn%20exchange%20of%20views%20was%20also%20held%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20upcoming%20G20%20summit%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Russian%20President%20has%20not%20travelled%20outside%20Central%20Asia%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20in%20February%202022.%20The%20only%20exception%20was%20a%20visit%20to%20Tehran%20in%20July%202022%2C%20where%20he%20also%20held%20a%20meeting%20with%20Turkish%20President%20Recep%20Tayyip%20Erdogan.%20He%20also%20didn%E2%80%99t%20attend%20the%20last%20G-20%20summit%20in%20Indonesia%2C%20as%20well%20as%20the%20recent%20BRICS%20meeting%20in%20South%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPutin%20skipped%20the%20BRICS%20summit%20due%20to%20an%20active%20warrant%20issued%20against%20him%20by%20the%20International%20Criminal%20Court%20(ICC).%20The%20ICC%20has%20levied%20war%20crime%20accusations%20against%20him%20in%20relation%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20although%20the%20Kremlin%20has%20refuted%20these%20claims.%20Given%20South%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20affiliation%20with%20the%20ICC%2C%20it%20would%20have%20been%20obliged%20to%20apprehend%20Putin%20had%20he%20been%20present%20on%20its%20soil.%20However%2C%20India%20is%20not%20a%20signatory%20of%20the%20statute%20of%20Rome.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20international%20summits%20that%20he%20has%20skipped%20so%20far%2C%20Putin%20attended%20them%20virtually.%20He%20may%20do%20so%20even%20this%20time%20around%2C%20or%20may%20even%20send%20a%20recorded%20message.%20However%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20official%20word%20yet%20on%20how%20he%20will%20make%20his%20presence%20felt.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1693237407000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F06%2F30205904%2FNarendra_Modi_and_Vladimir_Putin_2022-09-16.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Fputin-dials-modi-conveys-his-inability-to-attend-upcoming-g20-summit-in-delhi%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Russian%20President%20has%20not%20travelled%20outside%20Central%20Asia%20since%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20in%20